<dl id="un1013am"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013am"> (NLI.3) 13(am)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Babylonian lore 7 heavens, 7 hells.</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> <mark>In Babylonian thought, Winckler says, &ldquo;there were seven heavens and seven hells.&rdquo;</mark> This belief is one of untraceable antiquity. Writing on this subject, Hommel remarks: &ldquo;The idea of the seven heavens seems to go back to the beginnings of Semitic culture.&rdquo; <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. Mead, &ldquo;On the Watch-Tower&rdquo; 293</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c07258a" href="../../../F/FF/fnbs/c07all.htm#c07258a">VI.C.07:258(a)</a> </dd> </dd></dl>
